The paper deals with motion planning for industrial robots in unstructured and cluttered environments, which is a core problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves using a 3D Convolutional Neural Network for identifying bottleneck regions in the planning scenario, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sampling-based motion planners, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
